This British retrospective captures two decades' worth of Snowy White's guitar magic. The 

album includes "Highway to the Sun" (from the album of the same name), "Renegade" and 

"Memory Pain" (from White's //stint with Thin Lizzy), the unedited version of Pink Floyd's 

"Pigs on the Wing" (on which White solos) and collaborations with Peter Green, Rick Wright 

and Al Stewart. ~ Heather Phares, All Music Guide - Heather Phares
Snowy White
British-born blues/rock guitarist Snowy White first became interested in music at age 11, 

when he heard urban blues performers like B.B. King, Otis Rush, and Buddy Guy, and was 

inspired to create his own clean, hard-edged style of British blues.
